The physical chararacteristics are definied here

1 : Rot MASS Density of the fluid in this volume in 3d or surface in 2d
2 : nu  FLUID VISCOSITY density of the fluid
3 : FOmega INTERNAL FORCES density
4 : INITIAL VELOCITIES in this volume in 3d or surface in 2d
5 : INITIAL PRESSURES in this volume in 3d or surface in 2d

All of them may be defined by constants or functions.

Attention to the unity of each fluid characteristic.
Cf http://hypertextbook.com/physics/matter/viscosity/

For the unsteady problem, the INITIAL velocities or/and pressures may be defined from
- the last computed velocities_pressures;
- the constant values or functions on the objet (the fluid)
- the constant values or functions on the VSLP (the volumes, surfaces, lines or points
  of the fluid)
with a priority to the Points, then after, the lines, then after the surfaces,
then after the volumes and finally, the object.

Type @; or escape to quit the actual Volume or Surface and to pass to the next.

